cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.SE. 

The paper deals with the automatic translation of natural language specifications into executable answer set programs, which involves natural language processing, artificial intelligence, and programming languages. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a bi-directional grammar, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing and computational linguistics, suggesting cs.LG as another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with the modification and verbalisation of the generated answer set programs, which involves software engineering and software development, suggesting cs.PL and cs.SE as additional possible sub-categories.
